This framework has 3 main processes:

* **Deep Learning Cycle:** : On a deeper level learning is about developing the capacity to reliably produce a certain quality of results. I.e. you can declare you've learnt bicycle riding if you only ride a bicycle once. This deep process encompasses 5 elements which reinforces each other. For e.g. if people believe the value of real listening, they create "check-in" practice or when people deevop dialogue skills, they become more appreciative of the people who depend on them and this strengthens relationships. It is easy to talk about culture as "the way things are". But this process helps us understand different elements of it. The important thing to notice is that, if you change one of these things the others change too albeit slowly.
* **Strategy Framework** This framework captures the 3 aspects of a coherent strategy. This point of view originates from "structuration". These three elements are:
  * Guiding Ideas: These are the ideas that accompany the strategy. They are most of the time rooted in governing concepts and principles (as well as purpose, vision and values).
  * Infrastructure Innovations: These include organizational infrastructure changes like formal roles, management structures. They determine how the energy flows in the system.
  * Theory, Tools & Methods: These are the elements people interact with e.g. different meeting styles, postmortems, kanban board, etc...
* **Iteration**: This is the way we model the progression of nature in time. Everything iterates wheter we are conciously act alongside it and decrease the gap between our vision and the current reality. Iterations give us a framework to continuously monitor the gaps we are trying to decrease.

